üü¢ BASIC MCQs (10)
1. A hash function primarily provides:
A. Confidentiality
B. Integrity
C. Authentication
D. Non-repudiation

2. Output of a hash function is called:
A. Ciphertext
B. Digest
C. Key
D. Plaintext

3. SHA stands for:
A. Secure Hash Algorithm
B. Standard Hash Algorithm
C. Simple Hash Algorithm
D. Strong Hash Algorithm

4. Which property ensures same input gives same hash?
A. Avalanche effect
B. Deterministic
C. Collision resistance
D. One-way

5. Which is a hashing algorithm?
A. AES
B. DES
C. SHA-256
D. RSA

6. Hash functions are:
A. Reversible
B. Two-way
C. One-way
D. Key-based

7. SHA-1 produces a hash of:
A. 64 bits
B. 128 bits
C. 160 bits
D. 256 bits

8. SHA-256 belongs to:
A. SHA-0
B. SHA-1 family
C. SHA-2 family
D. SHA-3 family

9. HMAC uses:
A. Only hash function
B. Hash + secret key
C. Public key
D. Symmetric encryption only

10. Hashing is mainly used to ensure:
A. Confidentiality
B. Integrity
C. Availability
D. Compression

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE MCQs (10)
11. Which property prevents finding original message from hash?
A. Determinism
B. Pre-image resistance
C. Collision resistance
D. Diffusion

12. Avalanche effect means:
A. Small input change ‚Üí large hash change
B. Hash can be reversed
C. Same hash for different input
D. Encryption strength

13. Which SHA version is considered insecure today?
A. SHA-512
B. SHA-384
C. SHA-256
D. SHA-1

14. HMAC provides protection against:
A. Replay attack
B. Message tampering
C. Brute force
D. DoS

15. Why HMAC is stronger than plain hash?
A. Larger output
B. Uses secret key
C. Faster computation
D. Public key usage

16. Which is NOT a property of secure hash?
A. Collision resistance
B. Pre-image resistance
C. Key exchange
D. Deterministic output

17. HMAC is commonly used in:
A. Digital certificates
B. Network protocols (TLS, IPsec)
C. File compression
D. Disk partitioning

18. Which attack targets hash collisions?
A. Brute force
B. Birthday attack
C. MITM
D. Side-channel

19. Hashing passwords is better than encrypting because:
A. Faster
B. Hash cannot be reversed
C. Smaller size
D. Uses public key

20. SHA-2 family includes:
A. SHA-1 only
B. SHA-224, SHA-256, SHA-384, SHA-512
C. SHA-3 only
D. MD5

üî∫ ADVANCED MCQs (10)
21. HMAC construction prevents which weakness of plain hash?
A. Determinism
B. Length-extension attack
C. Collision
D. Hash size limitation

22. Which is true about SHA-3?
A. Based on MD construction
B. Based on Keccak
C. Same as SHA-2
D. Deprecated

23. In HMAC, two keys (ipad & opad) are used to:
A. Increase speed
B. Prevent cryptographic attacks
C. Encrypt data
D. Reduce hash size

24. Which attack exploits mathematical properties of hashes?
A. Replay attack
B. Birthday attack
C. MITM
D. Sniffing

25. Which statement is correct?
A. Hash ensures confidentiality
B. Hash ensures integrity
C. Hash ensures availability
D. Hash ensures encryption

26. Digital signatures use hash functions to:
A. Encrypt message
B. Reduce message size before signing
C. Generate keys
D. Authenticate network

27. Which is MOST secure today?
A. MD5
B. SHA-1
C. SHA-256
D. CRC32

28. HMAC uses which type of key?
A. Public key
B. Private key
C. Symmetric secret key
D. Session key only

29. Which of the following is NOT a use of hashing?
A. File integrity checking
B. Password storage
C. Key exchange
D. Digital signatures

30. CCEE TRAP in hashing questions usually tests:
A. Hash vs encryption difference
B. SHA family confusion
C. HMAC purpose
D. All of the above

